# Seattle Terrain Analysis

## Project Overview

This project demonstrates terrain visualization and analysis using USGS 1 Meter DEM data within QGIS.

The workflow included:

- DEM mosaic creation
- DEM clipping to study area
- Hillshade generation
- Contour extraction (25 meter interval)
- Terrain visualization using elevation tinting
- Cartographic map production

## Study Area

King County, Washington

## Data Sources

- USGS 1 Meter Digital Elevation Model (DEM)
- OpenStreetMap Basemap

## Software

- QGIS 3.44
- GDAL
- QGIS Layout Manager

## Analysis Workflow

### 1. DEM Mosaic

Merged multiple USGS DEM tiles into a continuous elevation surface.

### 2. Study Area Extraction

Clipped DEM to the project boundary.

### 3. Hillshade Generation

Created hillshade raster to enhance terrain visualization.

### 4. Contour Generation

Generated contour lines at 25 meter intervals.

### 5. Terrain Visualization

Combined elevation tinting, hillshade, and contours into a final cartographic product.

